<subSubSection lastPageId="164" lastPageNumber="165" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="163" pageNumber="164">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 150" captionStartId="F150" captionText="Figure 150. Distribution of Conostegia dissitiflora." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure150" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96508" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">150</figureCitation>
). Endemic to south Pacific Costa Rica, mainly in the Golfo Dulce region and the Osa Peninsula but also towards to mountains on the road from San Vito de Coto Brus to Ciudad Neily, from sea level to 660 m elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="973951" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure150" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96508" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" start="Figure 150" startId="F150">
