Distribution of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia dissitiflora" order="Myrtales" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dissitiflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Conostegia dissitiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph lastPageId="164" lastPageNumber="165" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia dissitiflora" order="Myrtales" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dissitiflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Conostegia dissitiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a distinctive species on the basis of its overall glabrous, plinerved, sessile leaves, and 5-merous flowers with an irregularly rupturing calyx. 
<bibRefCitation author="Almeda, F" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences" pageId="239" pageNumber="240" pagination="137 - 150" refId="B2" refString="Almeda, F, 1989a. Five new berry-fruited species of tropical American Melastomataceae. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 46: 137 - 150" title="Five new berry-fruited species of tropical American Melastomataceae." volume="46" year="1989 a">Almeda (1989a)</bibRefCitation>
discussed an unusual feature of this species which is the presence of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“anisomorphic”">&quot;anisomorphic&quot;</normalizedToken>
stamens, with the larger set of stamens positioned opposite the petals. The 
<pageBreakToken pageId="164" pageNumber="165" start="start">three</pageBreakToken>
flowering populations observed had flowers with exserted styles as is common in section 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="164" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Geniculatae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="164" pageNumber="165">Geniculatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Interestingly, when 
<bibRefCitation author="Almeda, F" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences" pageId="239" pageNumber="240" pagination="137 - 150" refId="B2" refString="Almeda, F, 1989a. Five new berry-fruited species of tropical American Melastomataceae. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 46: 137 - 150" title="Five new berry-fruited species of tropical American Melastomataceae." volume="46" year="1989 a">Almeda (1989a)</bibRefCitation>
described this species, he compared it to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia cinnamomea" order="Myrtales" pageId="164" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cinnamomea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="164" pageNumber="165">Conostegia cinnamomea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which it falls very close to in the molecular phylogeny. The two share almost complete glabrosity and plinerved venation. 
<bibRefCitation author="Almeda, F" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences" pageId="239" pageNumber="240" pagination="137 - 150" refId="B2" refString="Almeda, F, 1989a. Five new berry-fruited species of tropical American Melastomataceae. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 46: 137 - 150" title="Five new berry-fruited species of tropical American Melastomataceae." volume="46" year="1989 a">Almeda (1989a)</bibRefCitation>
discussed similar problems in placing 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia dissitiflora" order="Myrtales" pageId="164" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dissitiflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="164" pageNumber="165">Conostegia dissitiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Cogniaux’s">Cogniaux's</normalizedToken>
sections as he encountered placing 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia calocoma" order="Myrtales" pageId="164" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calocoma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="164" pageNumber="165">Conostegia calocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The problems arose because staminal characters including anther shape and lack of stamen appendages suggested section 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="164" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Amblyarrhena">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="164" pageNumber="165">Amblyarrhena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but a fused calyx suggested section 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="164" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Laceraria">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="164" pageNumber="165">Laceraria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
